3>(8/14/02 9:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1478.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Eye of Zomm tactics</span><hr size=1> Howdy all, how do you use the Eye of Zomm effectively as a mage? Is it just for exploring? Can you hit something around a corner you can see with the eye? Do you use it for crowd control? What's it's secret reason for being? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=xalmat>Xalmat</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#333333>(8/15/02 12:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1478.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Eye of Zomm tactics</span><hr size=1> It's most famous use is for targeting Captain Rottgrime :)<br>
<br>
Sometimes in an unfamiliar dungeon I use Eye of Zomm for targeting hard-to-reach mobs. Sometimes you can't click on them, but hitting F8 works. /shrug<br>
<br>
Eye of Zomm is good for scouting around corners where mobs can see invis, especially if you don't have a monk or rogue to pull. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubaisblackfingers.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BaisBlackfingers</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#333333>(8/15/02 1:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1478.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Eye of Zomm tactics</span><hr size=1> It's also something to bloody do in Sky- 'cuz the eyes fly.  Not lev, actually fly, meaning you can sneak peaks at the next island while your raid leaders are working shtuff out. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ujochangaladar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jochan Galadar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 488<br> <font color=#333333>(8/15/02 3:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1478.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Eye of Zomm tactics</span><hr size=1>     Good as a scouting tool.  In some dungeons, the eye can be forced to warp to another area of the dungeon.  Many limitations with this spell, tho.  Short duration, can't swim, can't jump and move at the same time.  Can sometimes be used as a last resort CoH invite tool....  but it's too random to be reliable. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uadawen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adawen</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(8/15/02 4:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1478.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Eye of Zomm tactics</span><hr size=1> If you have a druid/ranger in your group, they can be useful for targetting mobs to harmony in a few zones.  Umbral plains caves is the best use of this. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukathodos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kathodos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 79<br> <font color=#333333>(8/15/02 6:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1478.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.battle.net/war3/images/human/units/animations/waterelement.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Eye of Zomm tactics</span><hr size=1> Eye of Zomm (30 second Eye) and Eye of Tallon (60 second Eye+Invis+Glimpse) used to be near useless to a Magician because:<br>
1. You could not cast the eye while you had a pet up.<br>
2. The Eyes are level 1 mobs, and would aggro any monster they passed anywhere near, causing that mob to slay the eye, then charge and usually slay you.<br>
3.  Eye of Tallon's invis actually invis's the caster, and causes any pet you have up at the time to die.  This makes the spell useless to mages in most circumstances.<br>
<br>
1 &amp; 2 are no longer the case.  Eyes can be cast while you have a pet up, and are non-aggro.<br>
<br>
Do the Temple of Solusk Ro &quot;Clay Bracelet&quot; quest, and you get instant click Eye of Zomm, unlimited charges, inventory castable, Magician only.<br>
<br>
I personally used it in outdoor zones to target mobs behind rocks or ruins, and cast through the wall (you can do this in outdoor zones) to pull them out solo, where if I'd had to walk into the ruins I would have been jumped by the mob and his friends inside.<br>
<br>
Also great in dungeons or on raids when you always sit at the same old camp, while the monks go off to pull.  Most classes will never see anything beyond that camp, unless they can bind sight, or use Eye of Zomm/Eye of Tallon.<br>
<br>
Also great to cast for a mob that SK's and Necro's can lifetap.  A Magician with a Clay Bracelet and a Necro are their own mana factory.  Mage TRods, Necro lichs and pumps Mage health, then lifetaps eyes until they have their own health back. <p><FONT SIZE="3" COLOR=#FFFFFF FACE="Comic Sans MS, Sans-Serif, Courier New, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">
