<br>
Heheh. This may be entirely situational but I'd like to share an eye of zomm episode I had when playing my kid brother's 49 mage at a raid he couldn't attend (well not really kid, he's in college). <br>
<br>
Basically, the guild had a wipe-out past the KPC room when someone apparently trained the entire area on us. At least half didn't make it. By the time ppl regrouped, the dang things had already respawned and a lot of us were nakkid.<br>
<br>
Basically, I parked my toon up against a corridor wall, knowing that most of the bodies were on the other side. I cast eye of zomms, and had them go around and target each body so I can &quot;summon&quot; them through the wall. Since the eye is ignored by MOBs, I was safe. I got most of the bodies this way and took a shaman friend with me to secure a couple more further away (couldn't reach). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uadonhiram.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adonhiram</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 110<br> <font color=#333333>(8/17/02 6:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1478.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Eye of Zomm tactics</span><hr size=1> Another nice thing about our Clay Bracelet (which stats suck of course, but inventory castable) is that the Eye is insta-click. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=zeem>Zeem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 310<br> <font color=#333333>(8/17/02 3:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1478.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Getting replacment...</span><hr size=1> Totaly awesome for getting more people to a raid or group.<br>
I think I can get replacement to any place in Ssra just using an eye (well .. except Emp level...). <br>
The bad part is that our guilds become so used to us mages handling getting latecommers by ourself that they expect us to do it, that suck alot then only way to get to entrance is to use Eye of Talon, the invis part offf that spell totaly suck. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uailees.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ailees</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ikebana-toulouse.com/maitres/ailees.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 598<br> <font color=#333333>(8/18/02 1:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1478.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.ikebana-toulouse.com/citation/ailee-ep2.jpg width=130 height=164></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Getting replacment...</span><hr size=1> eyes of talon still kills pet, doesn't it ?<br>
